Docker Utility Commands
******************************
1.To enter into the runnning conatainer

 command : docker attach <container-name> or <conatiner-id>

 exapmle : docker attach test

2.Create a image from modified Container

 command : docker commit -m "msg" continer-name image-name

 example : docker commit -m "installed-appache" test apche-httpd

3.Copy the files from local to container and container local 
   
 local to container:

 command : docker cp file-name container-name:/location

 example : docker cp aws-setup test:/opt

 container to local:

 command : docker cp container-name:location .

 example : docker cp test:/opt/aws-setup .

 ":" is a separator
 "." is a current directory

 4.Only Create Container
  
  command : docker create <container-name> <image-name>

  Here,container is only created ,But not in up state

  example : docker create --name test nginx
  
  check : docker ps -a

  now

  docker start <container>

  docker start test

  check : docker ps

  